column26:
i was scared to break it;
i often had to compromise;
the program was impressive, i could sense some intelligence;
i felt like the program could cope with my natural use of language, but that it is very bad at understanding my intent. for example, answering "no" to a yes/no question was interpreted as a yes;
it felt like each conversation was going through the same questions. a chatbot then seems unnecessary (as a simple web form would be a better way to input the same information, for example);
